___________________________________________________Pointers_____________________________________________________

                                         : Pointer memory location :
Pointer Example 

   	  | 5 |       | 10 |      | 50 |  ======> pointer value 
     ptr[0]       ptr[1]       ptr[2]  ======> pointer location to be stored 
 
  
Genral syntax:

datatype *var_name;
int *ptr; 




Example of above 

# include < bits.h > or <stdc.h> // any one can be use

void PointerGroup()  
 
 {
	int value[3] = {5,10,50}; // pointer value   (1)
	
	//declare pointers
	int *ptr;  		//  pointer 
        
	//Assign pointer to variable 
	ptr = value;	   	// assign pointer     (2) 
	
	ptr = val;
	count <<"element value of pointers are">>;
	count <<"ptr[0]","ptr[1]","ptr[2]">>
	
	return;
}

int main()
{
	PointerGroup()
	return 0;
}







output :

	element of array are : 5 ,10, 50







